snippet: Political compromises and economic help from the European Union could ease the crisis that continues to deepen.
abstract: Editorial criticizes Ukrainian Pres Viktor Yanukovich for ordering security police to clear antigovernment demonstrators' encampment in Kiev, which has plunged country deeper into crisis; warns only a negotiated political compromise will resolve the conflict; urges the European Union to help Ukraine economically.
lead_paragraph: Political compromises and economic help from the European Union could ease the crisis that continues to deepen.
